  "commentary": "With SPX at 6546.63 sitting right in the heart of massive negative gamma walls (6550 at -17.7B, 6545 at -11.3B), dealers are forced to buy this dip aggressively as their short gamma positions require them to chase momentum. The breakout regime with -127.6B total GEX means any directional move will be amplified by dealer hedging, and the wall_break/gex_surge events suggest we just punched through key resistance that's now flipping to amplifying support. Watch 6550 as the critical level - above it dealers flip to selling pressure toward 6580 max positive gamma, but sustained breaks below trigger cascading dealer buying through the 6540-6525 negative gamma cluster.\n\nBottom line: expect violent swings with dealers amplifying whatever direction the market wants to go.",
